      "description": "When conversation history approaches the model token limit, automatically summarize the oldest messages with the AI, persist them to the session archive on disk, replace them with a compact notice in the active context, and allow retrieval via /recall or a recall_context tool.",
      "details": "## Problem\nThe current trimming strategy (count-based + token-budget) simply drops old messages when context fills up. This permanently loses potentially important conversation history. Users working on long coding sessions frequently lose earlier decisions, file edits, and reasoning chains.\n\n## Goal\nImplement a four-stage context lifecycle that replaces blind dropping with intelligent summarization:\n\n1. DETECT — when estimated prompt tokens exceed `compression_threshold` (default 75%) of `max_context_tokens`, trigger compression.\n2. SUMMARIZE — take the oldest `compression_chunk_ratio` (default 40%) of messages and make a fast API call to produce a bullet-point summary + key_facts list.\n3. ARCHIVE — persist the full raw messages + summary to disk at `~/.grok/sessions/{session_id}/archives/chunk_NNN.json` and update an `index.json`.\n4. REPLACE — remove the archived messages from `session.messages` and insert a compact system-role archive-notice message (~50 tokens) so the model knows the history exists and how to recall it.\n\n## Archive Notice Format (injected into active context)\n```\n[Context Archive #N | {timestamp}]\nSummary: {2-3 sentence AI summary of what was discussed/done}.\nKey facts: {bullet list}.\nSay \"recall archive N\" or type `/recall N` to restore this context.\n```\n\n## Storage Layout\n```\n~/.grok/sessions/{session_id}/\n  episode.json          (existing — end-of-session metadata)\n  transcript.json       (existing — full raw transcript)\n  archives/\n    index.json          (list of chunk IDs + token count)\n    chunk_001.json      (raw messages + AI summary)\n    chunk_002.json\n    ...\n```\n\n## New Rust Modules\n- `src/memory/context_archive.rs` — `ContextChunk`, `ContextArchive` structs + atomic disk I/O.\n- `src/memory/context_compressor.rs` — `ContextCompressor` that calls the Grok API to summarize a message batch.\n\n## New Config Fields (AcpConfig in src/config/mod.rs)\n```toml\n# Master switch — disable to revert to old drop-only behaviour.\nauto_compress = true\n# Fraction of max_context_tokens at which compression fires (0.0–1.0).\ncompression_threshold = 0.75\n# Fraction of current non-system messages compressed per event (0.0–1.0).\ncompression_chunk_ratio = 0.40\n```\n\n## Integration Point\nLayer 4 is added to `handle_chat_completion` in `src/acp/mod.rs`, after the existing three layers (per-message truncation, count trim, token-budget trim).\n\n## New Slash Commands (src/acp/slash_commands.rs)\n- `/recall N` — retrieve chunk N back into active context as a system message.\n- `/archives` — list all archived chunks for this session (ID, timestamp, token count, one-line summary).\n\n## New Tool (src/tools/ or src/acp/tools.rs)\n- `recall_context { chunk_id }` — allows the AI itself to pull an archived chunk back in when it detects it needs earlier information. Returns the summary + key_facts; the full raw messages are injected as a system message.",
