      "description": "Update all model references, capabilities, and context-management logic to fully leverage grok-4.3's 1,000,000-token context window while keeping backward compatibility with grok-3 (256 k) and grok-2 (131 k).",
      "details": "## Background\ngrok-4.3 is now the default model and exposes a 1,048,576-token context window — roughly 4× the grok-3 window.  The current code has several hardcoded or config-defaulted values that are tuned for grok-3 (256 k) and must be updated.\n\n## Changes Required\n\n### 1. src/acp/mod.rs — create_capabilities()\n- Set `max_context_length: 1_048_576` (up from 131_072).\n- Add `\"grok-4.3\"` as the first entry in `models` vec; keep grok-3, grok-3-mini, grok-2-vision-1212, grok-2 as fallbacks.\n- Add feature flags: `\"1m_context\"`, `\"vision\"` (grok-4.3 is multimodal).\n\n### 2. src/config/mod.rs — AcpConfig\n- Add new field `grok4_max_context_tokens: usize` (default: 950_000).  This is the soft budget for grok-4.x models — leaves 50 k headroom for response + tool definitions.\n- Rename/update the doc comment on `max_context_tokens` to clarify it applies to grok-3 and older.\n- Add `fn default_grok4_max_context_tokens() -> usize { 950_000 }`.\n- Update `AcpConfig::default()` to include the new field.\n\n### 3. src/acp/mod.rs — handle_chat_completion (Layer 3 token-budget trim)\n- Replace the single `max_ctx_tokens` lookup with model-aware selection:\n```rust\nlet max_ctx_tokens = model_context_budget(\n    &session.config.model,\n    self.config.acp.max_context_tokens,\n    self.config.acp.grok4_max_context_tokens,\n);\n```\n- Add free function `fn model_context_budget(model: &str, grok3_budget: usize, grok4_budget: usize) -> usize` that returns grok4_budget when `model.starts_with(\"grok-4\")`, else grok3_budget.\n- Apply the same model-aware budget in Layer 4 (compression threshold calculation).\n\n### 4. src/acp/mod.rs — SessionConfig::default()\n- Keep model as `\"grok-4.3\"`.\n- Raise `max_tokens` (output) to 16_384 — grok-4.3 supports higher output token limits.\n\n### 5. src/config/mod.rs — Config defaults\n- Update `default_max_tokens()` from 256_000 to 16_384 (this is the output-token budget; 256 k was erroneously set to match the input window).\n- Update comment on `default_max_context_tokens()` to clarify 220_000 is the grok-3 budget.\n\n### 6. config.example.toml + .grok/config.toml\n- Add `grok4_max_context_tokens = 950000` under `[acp]`.\n- Update comments to describe the model-selection logic.\n\n### 7. CONFIGURATION.md\n- Add a \"Model Context Budgets\" section documenting grok-4.3 vs grok-3 limits.\n\n### 8. CHANGELOG.md\n- Add entry for v0.2.0 noting grok-4.3 default and 1 M context support.",
