      "description": "Add first-class support for grok-4.3 thinking/reasoning modes via the xAI API's reasoning_effort parameter.  Users can switch between Off / Low / High reasoning at runtime; thinking tokens are surfaced in the terminal UI and optionally persisted with session history.",
      "details": "## Background\nThe xAI API exposes a `reasoning_effort` field on chat completion requests for models that support extended thinking (grok-3-mini, grok-4.x).  Valid values:\n- `\"none\"` — standard response, no internal reasoning trace.\n- `\"low\"` — light reasoning; faster and cheaper.\n- `\"high\"` — deep reasoning; highest quality, slower, higher token cost.\nThe response may include a `thinking` or `reasoning_content` field in `choices[0].message` containing the model's internal chain-of-thought.\n\n## Changes Required\n\n### 1. src/config/mod.rs\n- Add `ThinkingMode` enum:\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]\n#[serde(rename_all => \"snake_case\")]\npub enum ThinkingMode {\n    #[default]\n    Off,    // reasoning_effort = \"none\" (not sent for non-reasoning models)\n    Low,    // reasoning_effort = \"low\"\n    High,   // reasoning_effort = \"high\"\n}\n```\n- Add `thinking_mode: ThinkingMode` field to `AcpConfig` with `#[serde(default)]` and `default_thinking_mode` fn returning `ThinkingMode::Off`.\n\n### 2. src/acp/mod.rs — SessionConfig\n- Add `pub thinking_mode: ThinkingMode` field to `SessionConfig`.\n- Update `SessionConfig::default()` to set `thinking_mode: ThinkingMode::Off`.\n\n### 3. src/grok_client_ext.rs — GrokClient::chat_completion_with_history\n- Add `reasoning_effort: Option<&str>` parameter (or `thinking_mode: Option<ThinkingMode>`).\n- If `Some` and not `ThinkingMode::Off`, append `\"reasoning_effort\": \"low\"|\"high\"` to the JSON request body.\n- Since grok_api v0.1.7's builder may not expose this field, inject it by either:\n  (a) Adding a `.reasoning_effort(val)` builder method to the local grok_api crate (`../grok_crate/grok_api/src/client.rs`), or\n  (b) Adding an `extra_body` field to the builder that merges a `serde_json::Map` into the request body before serialization.\n- Preferred: option (a) — add `reasoning_effort: Option<String>` to the request builder in grok_api.\n\n### 4. src/grok_client_ext.rs — MessageWithFinishReason + response parsing\n- Extend `MessageWithFinishReason` with `pub thinking_content: Option<String>`.\n- In `convert_response_to_message_with_finish_reason`: extract `choices[0].message.reasoning_content` or `choices[0].message.thinking` if present and store in `thinking_content`.\n- Forward `thinking_content` back through `handle_chat_completion` → display layer.\n\n### 5. src/acp/mod.rs — handle_chat_completion\n- Pass `session.config.thinking_mode` (converted to `Option<&str>`) when calling `chat_completion_with_history`.\n- After receiving the response, if `thinking_content` is Some, prepend it to the assistant message as a fenced block:\n```\n<details><summary>🧠 Thinking…</summary>\n\n{thinking_content}\n\n</details>\n```\n- Emit a `debug!()` log with token count of thinking content (len / 4).\n\n### 6. src/acp/slash_commands.rs — /think command\n- Add `SlashCommand::Think { mode: ThinkingMode }`.\n- Parse `/think` → list current mode.\n- Parse `/think off` → ThinkingMode::Off.\n- Parse `/think low` → ThinkingMode::Low.\n- Parse `/think high` → ThinkingMode::High.\n- Call a new `GrokAcpAgent::set_thinking_mode(session_id, mode)` method.\n- Return a `BuiltinResult::Handled(msg)` describing the change.\n\n### 7. src/acp/mod.rs — set_thinking_mode()\n- Add `pub async fn set_thinking_mode(&self, session_id: &SessionId, mode: ThinkingMode) -> Result<()>`.\n\n### 8. src/main.rs / CLI chat command\n- Add `--thinking <off|low|high>` flag to the `chat` subcommand.\n- Pass it through `SessionConfig` when starting a chat session.\n\n### 9. Config files + docs\n- Add `thinking_mode = \"off\"` to `[acp]` in `config.example.toml` with a comment.\n- Document in `CONFIGURATION.md`.\n- Add CHANGELOG entry.\n\n## Network / Starlink Considerations\nThinking mode requests take significantly longer (especially `high`).  Ensure:\n- `timeout_secs` is respected (already configured for long operations).\n- The existing Starlink retry loop covers thinking-mode requests without special changes (they're the same HTTP call, just longer).",
