      "testStrategy": "1. `cargo build --release` and `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` pass.\n2. Unit test: `ThinkingMode` serialises to/from `\"off\"`, `\"low\"`, `\"high\"` correctly.\n3. Unit test: `SessionConfig` default has `thinking_mode = ThinkingMode::Off`.\n4. Integration test (with GROK_API_KEY): start session, send `/think high`, verify session config updated, make a simple request, verify response includes a `<details>` block with thinking content (or gracefully skips it if the model returns none).\n5. Slash command test: parse `/think low` → produces `SlashCommand::Think { mode: ThinkingMode::Low }`.\n6. `--thinking high` CLI flag sets `SessionConfig::thinking_mode` before first call.\n7. No regression on sessions using `ThinkingMode::Off` (default).",
