      "testStrategy": "Phase A: Doc/acp-migration-map.md exists with every protocol.rs type classified.\nPhase B: after each subtask, cargo test --lib passes all existing tests (45 slash-command + all other lib tests). Integration smoke-test with Zed: /bayes show, /think high, 3-turn chat — behaviour identical to pre-migration. cargo clippy --all-targets zero warnings.\nPhase C per feature — 111.5: kill grok mid-session, relaunch, send session/load, confirm history+goal restored. 111.6: trigger a file-write tool, confirm Zed shows structured permission dialog. 111.7: fork conversation in Zed, confirm independent branch. 111.8: connect plain MCP client to ACP stdio, list tools — all 32 visible.",
