      "description": "Design and implement a Text-Graph Synergy RAG engine for grok-cli using a hybrid tree-sitter + syn parser to build a semantic-entity project graph (structs, enums, traits, impls, functions, modules), coupled with embeddings and hybrid retrieval (BM25 + vectors) to drive graph-aware, retrieval-aware context compression and LLM prompting.",
      "details": "## Background\nCurrent grok-cli context handling includes context discovery and AI-powered summarization/archiving, but it is linear and text-only. The next step is a Text-Graph Synergy RAG (TGS-RAG) engine that couples a semantic project graph with embeddings and hybrid retrieval. The goal is to retrieve minimal, highly relevant context for each request by traversing a semantic entity graph (structs, enums, traits, impls, functions, modules) and combining it with vector search and BM25.\n\nThis epic uses a hybrid parsing approach: tree-sitter for fast, incremental file/function boundaries and syn for deep semantic extraction. The resulting graph will power graph-expanded retrieval, reranking, and Context Compression 2.0.\n\n## Scope\n- Build a semantic-entity project graph for Rust (and later, language-agnostic hooks).\n- Integrate embeddings + BM25 hybrid retrieval.\n- Implement graph-expanded retrieval and reranking.\n- Implement Context Compression 2.0 (retrieval-aware pruning + summarization).\n- Integrate with ACP sessions, Session DNA, and existing context-discovery pipeline.\n- Add configuration, docs, and tests.\n\n## Out of Scope\n- Non-Rust language-specific parsers (future tasks).\n- Full MCP-based external knowledge sources (future tasks).",
