      "description": "Add an “explorer mode” to the existing Grok‑CLI agent so that the same LLM can act as a repo explorer when requested, but still returns compact evidence instead of full file contents.",
      "details": "## Goal\nAdd an “explorer mode” to the existing Grok‑CLI agent so that the same LLM can act as a repo explorer when requested, but still returns compact evidence instead of full file contents.\n\n## Scope\nNo new model. Use the existing Grok‑CLI LLM with a different system prompt + tool policy.\n\nNew mode: AgentMode::Explorer\n\nActivated explicitly by the runtime/planner when repo exploration is needed.\n\n## Architecture\nEnum extension:\nenum AgentMode { Normal, Explorer }\n\nEntry point:\nfn run_agent(mode: AgentMode, session: &mut Session, ...)\n\nExplorer system prompt:\n“You are a repository exploration agent. You may only use tools to list files, read files, and search text. Your final answer must be a JSON object with file paths and line ranges relevant to the query. Do not propose code changes.”\n\nOutput schema:\nSame RepoEvidence / RepoEvidenceItem structure as Task 159 (reuse types across projects if you like).\n\n## Tool usage\nTools: reuse existing Grok‑CLI tools:\n- fs_glob\n- fs_read\n- fs_grep (or equivalent)\n\nParallelism:\nUse your existing tool loop but allow multiple outstanding tool calls when the LLM requests them in a single turn.\n\nResult shaping:\nAfter the explorer‑mode run completes, parse the JSON into RepoEvidence and pass that to the normal‑mode agent as context.\n\n## Integration with Grok‑CLI runtime\nPlanner change:\nWhen a task requires repo understanding (e.g., user asks “Where is X implemented?” or “Add feature Y to the HTTP router”), the planner:\n- Spawns an explorer‑mode run with a focused query.\n- Receives RepoEvidence.\n- Starts a normal‑mode run with RepoEvidence injected into the system/context messages.\n\nSession/messages:\nExplorer run is a separate sub‑session or a tagged phase in the same session:\n- Tag messages with phase: Explorer vs phase: Main.\n- Only the final evidence is carried over, not the entire explorer conversation.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\nFunctional:\n[ ] AgentMode::Explorer can be invoked directly via a CLI flag (e.g., --explore \"where is the router?\") for debugging.\n[ ] Planner can automatically invoke explorer mode before complex coding tasks.\n[ ] Explorer responses are valid JSON and parse into RepoEvidence.\n\nBehavioral:\n[ ] In explorer mode, the LLM never proposes patches or calls write tools (verified via logs).\n[ ] Main mode receives only compact evidence, not full file contents, unless it explicitly asks for them later.\n\nPerformance:\n[ ] For a representative Grok‑CLI coding task, total tokens in the main run are reduced vs. baseline (even if overall tokens are similar, main context is cleaner).",
      "id": 162,
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "done",
      "subtasks": [],
      "testStrategy": "1. Run with --explore flag and verify explorer JSON output.\n2. Trigger planner on a repo query and confirm evidence injection into main mode.\n3. Verify no write tools or patch proposals in explorer mode logs.\n4. Measure token reduction in main run context.",
      "title": "Mode-switched FastContext-style explorer using main LLM"
    },
